name: Bali Villa Nujum
address: Jalan Raya Gili Manuk-Seririt, RV3G+RWR, Kalisada, Tegallengah-Lovina, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81153, Indonesia
review 1: Really a great villa directly on the beach. The staff can cook very good. This villa is very spacious and beautiful. We like to come back to this place , we can not wait. The villa is in the north of Bali, the best place to stay. Far away from the crowdy south. Will you have a tropical holiday this is the right place.
review 2: Absolutely perfect. Good location, great stuff, clean and lovely decorated Villa. Full recommended for some days in North Bali

name: Betutu Ayam Kampung Bu Eka
address: RV2F+CXW, Jl. Singaraja-Gilimanuk, Kalisada, Kec. Seririt, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81153, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice cozy outdoor place. One of the cleanest place to eat along the way from Gilimanuk to Denpasar.
The food is average, but if you are looking for halal, I think this is one of the few places.

name: LESEHAN IKAN BAKAR RIANG
address: Jln seririt gilimanuk km 8 desa kalisade kec seririt Kalisada Kota buleleng, Kalisada, Kec. Seririt, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81155, Indonesia
review 1:
Timing was on our side when we, by chance, ended up choosing the casual roadside Warung Ikan Bakar Riang. Next to us - and to our absolute delight - a local fitness team celebrated the birthday of one of its members with laid-back Karaoke. I could imagine that this place generally is more quiet, but the fact that these things can happen alone is worth 5 stars for the ambiance.
The food itself was amazing. We went for the classics with Nasi Campur and Nasi Goreng which were so good that I had to order another round Goreng. We received some free fruit with the food while the table next to us continued taking group photos and singing along to what I can only describe as Balinese 90s pop ballads.
Needless to say, we loved this place.
review 2: great place, good people, tasty foods
